cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.DS, cs.AI

The paper deals with the analysis of information space, particularly web-resources, social networks, and blogs, which falls under the scope of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and social networks (cs.SI). The mathematical principles used for information operations recognition involve nonlinear dynamics, complex networks theory, and information and mathematical modeling, which are relevant to data science (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the application of expert estimation theory and decision-making support to information operation recognition falls under the scope of social computing (cs.SOC).
